H0.text: Incubation is the process by which birds keep their eggs warm while the embryos inside develop.

H1.text: Insulation is the process by which birds keep their eggs warm while the embryos inside develop.

H2.text: Spawning is the term for when birds keep their eggs warm while the embryos inside develop.

H3.text: Fertilization is what it is called when birds keep their eggs warm while the embryos inside develop.
